Oct 8 2009 	A Charming Vintage Hotel in Downtown San Francisco	We recently spent five days in The City by the Bay, and we were absolutely enchanted by our accommodations! The Hotel California is an older hotel just blocks from Union Square, and has maintained the elegance of its former days while updating itself in key matters. Our room was high-ceilinged, with ceiling fan and tall bay windows, and the staff had thoughtfully provided bathrobes for our use. There is an exercise room available, and wireless internet in the rooms (although it was fairly slow whenever I used my laptop). The decor is charming, with quotes about San Francisco and California painted on the walls in the lobby and above the crown moulding in our room. The staff is exemplary; everyone at the front desk was so helpful, giving us tips on restaurants and things to do, as well as walking-distance attractions. There is a very good restaurant/bar attached to the hotel, and they offer a free wine and cheese every evening from 5 to 6 pm. We had breakfast included in our room rate, which was a very good value, as otherwise it is $7.00 per person.The hotel's location is excellent, as it is right on one of the bus routes, and only 4 blocks away from the Powell/4th Street Cable Car terminus, where you can purchase MUNI tickets for 1, 3, or 7 days (a GREAT value!). If you haven't read this tip already: USE PUBLIC TRANSPORTATION IN THE CITY. Do NOTdrive your own car. Traffic is a nightmare, and parking is a migraine headache! We took the CalTrain to The City from the airport ($7.00 per person), and then paid $8.00 for a cab ride to the hotel. It was worth every penny!!	
