Aug 25 2009 	Most comfortable bed ever	My husband and I travelled to SF with another couple last week. We all really enjoyed the Hotel California which is close to shopping, tourist attractions, transportation, theatre, dining, and anything else you could possibly want or need. The hotel is very European and the beds are comfortable, maid service is excellent and very friendly, and the decor is tasteful. We loved the hardwood floors and quotes on the walls. There is lots to see and do in SF and transportation is relatively cheap. If anything, I would dismiss the hotel's dining recommendations and try out the Pacific Cafe at 7000 Geary Boulevard (at 34th Avenue, a $15 cab ride) or anywhere in Little Italy where late night dining/beverage options abound (we ate at Steps of Rome and Michelangelo's, a $10 cab ride). Both of these restaurants offered complimentary wine while we waited for a table. In the morning, make sure you go around the block from the hotel for breakfast crepes at Honey Honey. We went to see Wicked at the Orpheum Theatre and would highly recommend it.	
